<TEXT>

Mary Barra appointed as General Motors chief

<TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2013-12-10">December 10, 2013</TIMEX3>

The United States's largest car manufacturer General Motors <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2013-12-10">today</TIMEX3> named Mary Barra as its new chief executive.

Barra, 51, will be the first woman to lead a firm in the American auto industry.

She has been with General Motors for <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DURATION" value="P33Y">33 years</TIMEX3>, and is <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE" value="PRESENT_REF">currently</TIMEX3> the global head of product development.

She said in a statement :``With an amazing portfolio of cars and trucks and the strongest financial performance in <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE" value="PRESENT_REF">our recent history</TIMEX3>, <TIMEX3 tid="t6" type="DATE" value="XXXX-XX-XX">this</TIMEX3> is <TIMEX3 tid="t7" type="DATE" value="XXXX-XX-XX">an exciting time</TIMEX3> at <TIMEX3 tid="t8" type="DATE" value="PRESENT_REF">today</TIMEX3>'s GM.

